  <text>
    <front>
      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_6209_p1">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>HÔTEL BAUR <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
                        <placeName type="place" key="Zürich (Stadt)">ZÜRICH</placeName> </fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <p rend="left" xml:id="K_6209_p2">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>
        <hi rend="underline">Privat</hi>
      </p>
      <p rend="right" xml:id="K_6209_p3">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>23 Parliament Street
			<lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
                <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName> </p>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_6209_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
          <placeName type="place" key="Zürich (Stadt)">Zürich</placeName>
          <date when="1866-01-07">
            <choice>
                            <abbr>Jan<hi rend="sup">ry</hi> </abbr>
                            <expan>January (Januar)</expan>
                        </choice>
							7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1866</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_6209_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>Dear
				Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
            <div>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_6209_p6">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>Enclosed I forward you a letter <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>for your Committee, and as you must be <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>aware, it is
				difficult to discuss the matters <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>fully in that letter, from the
				fact of my <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>having little or no knowledge of your Committee <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>and not knowing whether they will agree with <lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>us, I
				am therefore naturally reluctant to enter <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>into matters which I
				otherwise would, from <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>any short
					acquaitance<note type="transcript">sic!</note> with you which has <lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>been most satisfactory to me, I with great <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>pleasure,
        unhesitatingly beg to offer you on <pb n="2"/>
                <lb xml:id="p2-l1"/>behalf of <choice>
                        <abbr>Mess<hi rend="sup">es</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Messieurs (Herren)</expan>
                    </choice> <persName type="person" key="Hudson James">Hudson</persName> Frankish and <choice>
                        <abbr>C<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan>
                    </choice> <lb xml:id="p2-l2"/>a directorship bearing in mind that <lb xml:id="p2-l3"/>Sir <persName type="person" key="Hudson James">James Hudson</persName> has already suggested <lb xml:id="p2-l4"/>you being one<!-- Transkription korrigiert, zuvor "obee", BF, 21.01.2015 -->, in addition I beg to add <lb xml:id="p2-l5"/>that any
				sum<!-- Transkription korrigiert, zuvor "sums", BF, 21.01.2015 --> or sums of money you <lb xml:id="p2-l6"/>have spent in the promotion of this great
					<lb xml:id="p2-l7"/>undertaking, it is only fair that you would <lb xml:id="p2-l8"/>at
				once be reimbursed, and while we <lb xml:id="p2-l9"/>undertake to do, I shall at all
				times be <lb xml:id="p2-l10"/>ready to render you any information and <lb xml:id="p2-l11"/>consult with you from time to time <lb xml:id="p2-l12"/>upon this matter, and any
				suggestions <lb xml:id="p2-l13"/>that you will make tending to the <lb xml:id="p2-l14"/>progress and the carrying out of this<!-- Transkription korrigiert, zuvor "thus", BF, 21.01.2015 --> <lb xml:id="p2-l15"/>affair I feel sure will be
				cheerfully <lb xml:id="p2-l16"/>listened to by Sir <persName type="person" key="Hudson James">J. Hudson</persName> and <choice>
                        <abbr>Co.</abbr>
                        <expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan>
                    </choice> <pb n="3"/>
                <lb xml:id="p3-l1"/>trusting that our acquaintance will <lb xml:id="p3-l2"/>lead to a
				favorable issue, which I have <lb xml:id="p3-l3"/>but little fear of </p>
    </div>
        </body>
    <back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_6209_p7">
                    <lb xml:id="p3-l4"/>I have the honour to remain <lb xml:id="p3-l5"/>dear Sir Your's truly </p>
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_6209_p8">
                    <lb xml:id="p3-l6"/>S. C. Frankish &amp; <choice>
                        <abbr>Co</abbr>
                        <expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan>
                    </choice> </p>
      </div>
      <postscript>
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_6209_p9">
                    <lb xml:id="p3-l7"/>
          <choice>
                        <abbr>P. S.</abbr>
                        <expan>Post Scriptum (nach dem Geschriebenen)</expan>
                    </choice> I should have
					sent you this <date when="1866-01-06">yesterday</date> <lb xml:id="p3-l8"/>but had to keep an unexpected engagement <lb xml:id="p3-l9"/>and was
					too late to send it on my <lb xml:id="p3-l10"/>return.</p>
      </postscript>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_6209_p10">
                    <lb xml:id="p3-l11"/>
          <hi rend="underline">S. C. F.</hi>
        </p>
      </div>
    </back>
